The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, held a briefing on March 23, 2009. During the briefing, he discussed the bank rescue program and answered questions about its effectiveness. He also addressed concerns about executive compensation, the involvement of private investors, and the role of the FDIC in the program. Additionally, Gibbs mentioned upcoming regulatory reform and the President's plans to address the American people in a press conference. He concluded by discussing the President's recent message to the Iranian people and his hopes for a change in relations.